<exercise checkit-seed="0018" checkit-slug="A2" checkit-title="Standard matrices">
  <statement>
    <ol>
      <li>Find the standard matrix for the linear transformation <m>S:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 4 </m> given by
              <me>S\left(  \left[\begin{array}{c}
x \\
y \\
z
\end{array}\right]  \right) =  \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \, x + 2 \, y + 6 \, z \\
x + 6 \, y + 8 \, z \\
x + 2 \, y + z \\
x + y
\end{array}\right] .</me></li>
      <li>Let <m>T:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 2 </m> be the linear transformation given by the standard matrix
              <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-4 &amp; 1 &amp; 7 \\
-5 &amp; 1 &amp; 8
\end{array}\right] .</me>
              Compute <m>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-8 \\
-1 \\
-6
\end{array}\right]  \right)</m>.
          </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-2 &amp; 2 &amp; 6 \\
1 &amp; 6 &amp; 8 \\
1 &amp; 2 &amp; 1 \\
1 &amp; 1 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-8 \\
-1 \\
-6
\end{array}\right]  \right)= \left[\begin{array}{c}
-11 \\
-9
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

